{"id":1278750078,"question_id":43,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"1Â month, 1Â week","timestamp":1717611491,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"106 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1278750078/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Multiply Strings","memory":"16.7 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def multiply(self, num1: str, num2: str) -> str:\n        if \"0\" in [num1, num2]:\n            return \"0\"\n        N, M = len(num1), len(num2)\n        res = [0] * (N+M)\n        num1, num2 = num1[::-1], num2[::-1]\n\n        for i in range(N):\n            for j in range(M):\n                digit = int(num1[i]) * int(num2[j])\n                res[i+j] += (digit)\n                res[i+j+1] += (res[i+j] // 10)\n                res[i+j] = res[i+j] % 10\n        \n        res = res[::-1]\n        start = 0\n        while start < (N+M) and res[start] == 0: start+=1 \n        res = map(str, res[start:])\n        return \"\".join(res)","compare_result":"","title_slug":"multiply-strings","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
